Package: quodlibet
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python:Depends}, python-pymad, python-pyvorbis, python-id3lib, python-glade2, quodlibet-ext (= ${Source-Version})
Suggests: albumart
Description: audio library manager and player for GTK+
 Quod Libet is a music player based around searching your audio library
 based on the values of the tags in it. It supports MP3, Ogg Vorbis, FLAC,
 and tracked (MOD/XM/IT) audio formats. Features include:
  - A simple user interface.
  - Searches based on regular expression matching.
  - Tag editing, including cross-format changes and mass editing.
  - Many supported tags, like "conductor", "performer", and "discnumber".
  - Shuffle, repeat, multimedia keys, Unicode support, a tray icon,
    album cover display, and other features found in most modern media
    players.
 .
 Quod Libet is written in Python and uses PyGTK+.

Package: quodlibet-ext
Architecture: any
Depends: quodlibet (= ${Source-Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: extensions for the Quod Libet audio player
 This package contains architecture-dependent extensions to Quod
 Libet.
 .
 Quod Libet is an audio player for GTK+ based around searching your
 audio collection's tags.
